<div><div><h2>Nestle India profit rises 30% on strong domestic sales</h2></div><div>nestle india ltd maker of maggi instant noodles and kit-kat chocolates reported a near 30% rise in quarterly profit on friday driven by higher domestic sales. profit came in at rs 446 crore in the quarter ended 30 september compared with rs 343 crore a year earlier. revenue from operations in the quarter grew nearly 17% to rs 2939 crore the indian unit of swiss food group nestle sa said. sales in the domestic market grew 17.5% to rs 2750 crore in the quarter while expenses rose 14.5%. .</div></div>